        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## La³⁺ Complexes with Carboxylic Acid Ligands — Stability Ranking\n\nBased on NIST SRD-46 data, here are the most stable La³⁺ complexes with carboxylic acid ligands, ranked by log β for the 1:1 ML complex at 25 °C and I = 0.1 mol/L:\n\n| Rank | Ligand | Ligand ID | log β (ML) | T (°C) | I (mol/L) |\n|------|--------|-----------|-----------|--------|-----------|\n| 1 | **EDTA** | ligand_6277 | **15.5** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 2 | **NTA** (nitrilotriacetic acid) | ligand_6165 | **10.36** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 3 | **Citric acid** | ligand_9058 | **8.0** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 4 | Isocitric acid | ligand_9057 | 7.2 | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 5 | Malic acid | ligand_8953 | 5.3 | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 6 | D-Tartaric acid | ligand_8955 | 5.1 | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 7 | Malonic acid | ligand_8873 | 4.7 | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 8 | Lactic acid | ligand_8641 | 3.3 | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 9 | Glycolic acid | ligand_8640 | 3.1 | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 10 | Acetic acid | ligand_8465 | 2.7 | 25 | 0.1 |\n\n*Source: NIST SRD-46*",
